image_analysis.description: A photograph of a large, ornate, double-leaf wooden door set within a stone archway. The doors feature rectangular paneling and a diamond-patterned lower section. Above the door is a semi-circular transom window with a circular pane in the center. An ornate black metal lantern hangs from the top of the archway in front of the transom. The surrounding walls are made of light-colored stone blocks. There is a small metal plate or buzzer system on the right stone pillar and some faint markings on the left pillar.

stamps_or_markings: Faint 'JE' marking on left stone pillar
